# Project: Wellness Shot Recommender (hackathon, mobile-first web)

## Stack

- Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind. NOT Next.js.
- No database, no Supabase, no auth, no login. Only server code is ONE Vercel
  serverless function for the AI feature.

## Data

- All catalog data is static in src/data/shots.ts. No backend fetch for catalog.

## Code

- Functional components + hooks, named exports, files <150 lines.
- Keep the app runnable and `npm run build` clean after every change.

## Design

- Mobile-first AND adaptive: great at ~390px, expands to a centered max-w-5xl
  layout on desktop. Never a stranded narrow column.
- White/off-white bg, fresh green primary, soft green accents, rounded-2xl.

## Secrets

- API keys NEVER in the repo. .env.local stays gitignored; real key lives in
  Vercel env vars; the function reads process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY.

## Bias

- Hackathon: prioritize a working, deployable build. Never leave it broken.
